      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): route p2p DM replies to user open_id instead of p2p group chat_id (fixes #83730)",
        "body": "## What\n\nRoute p2p DM replies to the sender's `open_id` instead of the p2p group's `chat_id`.\n\nWhen the Feishu bot receives a p2p (DM) message, the incoming `ctx.chatId` is the p2p group's `oc_xxx` identifier. The reply dispatcher was receiving this `oc_xxx` ID as its `chatId`, causing it to send replies via `im.message.create` with `receive_id_type=chat_id` targeting the p2p group. In WebSocket mode, this fails with `SUBSCRIPTION_NOT_FOUND` because the bot's WebSocket subscription does not cover the p2p group through the Feishu API subscription model.\n\nThe fix passes `feishuTo` (which resolves to `user:ou_xxx` for p2p chats) instead of `ctx.chatId` to `createFeishuReplyDispatcher` in both the broadcast and main dispatch paths. This routes replies through `im.message.create` with `receive_id_type=open_id`, which correctly delivers to the user.\n\n## Why\n\n- `feishuTo` is already computed at `bot.ts:853` as `isGroup ? 'chat:${ctx.chatId}' : 'user:${ctx.senderOpenId}'`\n- The reply dispatcher uses `chatId` as the send target for all non-reply messages (streaming, final text, cards)\n- For p2p chats, `ctx.chatId` is `oc_xxx` (the p2p group), but replies should target `user:ou_xxx` (the user)\n- `skipReplyToInMessages` already handles skipping the reply-to for p2p, but the send target was still wrong\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/bot.ts`: Pass `feishuTo` instead of `ctx.chatId` to `createFeishuReplyDispatcher` in both dispatch paths (broadcast at ~line 1601, main at ~line 1779)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** Feishu p2p DM replies fail with SUBSCRIPTION_NOT_FOUND when using WebSocket mode\n- **Environment tested:** macOS, OpenClaw main branch (6ca856ba), Feishu extension\n- **Steps run after the patch:** Verified `feishuTo` resolves to `user:ou_xxx` for p2p chats by tracing `bot.ts:853`. Confirmed `resolveReceiveIdType(\"user:ou_xxx\")` returns `\"open_id\"` via `targets.ts:70-72`. Ran all Feishu extension tests (bot: 87, reply-dispatcher: 82, channel: 61 — all pass).\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts\n ✓  extension-feishu  extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts (87 tests) 79ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  87 passed (87)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.test.ts\n ✓  extension-feishu  extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.test.ts (82 tests) 38ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  82 passed (82)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/channel.test.ts\n ✓  extension-feishu  extensions/feishu/src/channel.test.ts (61 tests) 13ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  61 passed (61)\n\n$ grep -n \"chatId: feishuTo\" extensions/feishu/src/bot.ts\n1601:              chatId: feishuTo,\n1779:          chatId: feishuTo,\n```\n- **Observed result after fix:** All 230 Feishu extension tests pass. The reply dispatcher now receives `user:ou_xxx` for p2p chats, which resolves to `receive_id_type=open_id` for message delivery.\n- **What was not tested:** Live Feishu WebSocket p2p interaction (requires Feishu app credentials and WebSocket connection).\n",
        "branch": "fix/feishu-p2p-reply-target",
